      "amount": "$875 million",
      "deadline": "2026-12-31",
      "category": "environmental"
    },
    {
      "obligation": "Environmental remediation reserve fund for legacy sites",
      "amount": "$1.2 billion",
      "deadline": "2028-12-31",
      "category": "environmental"
    },
    {
      "obligation": "Senior credit facility outstanding balance subject to environmental covenants",
      "amount": "$2.1 billion",
      "deadline": null,
      "category": "debt"
    }
  ],
  "summary": "Apex Energy Corporation faces substantial environmental and climate-related risks requiring $875 million in capital expenditures through 2026 for regulatory compliance. The company experienced $340 million in production losses from Hurricane Delphine in August 2024 and maintains $1.2 billion in environmental remediation reserves. Transition risks from renewable energy adoption and potential covenant breaches on $2.1 billion in debt represent significant ongoing challenges."
}

